description: You are given two 1-indexed integer arrays, nums and, changeIndices, having lengths n and m, respectively. Initially, all indices in nums are unmarked. Your task is to mark all indices in nums. In each second, s, in order from 1 to m (inclusive), you can perform one of the following operations: Return an integer denoting the earliest second in the range [1, m] when all indices in nums can be marked by choosing operations optimally, or -1 if it is impossible.
